bilingual.source: Weddings of the royal family always attract large audiences.
bilingual.target: 王室的婚礼总是吸引大量观众。

bilingual.source: The history of the royal family dates back several centuries.
bilingual.target: 王室的历史可以追溯到几个世纪前。

bilingual.source: The life of the royal family is a mystery to many people.
bilingual.target: 王室的生活对许多人来说是个谜。

bilingual.source: Britain's public sentiment about the countryside is fully backed by the royal family.
bilingual.target: 英国公众对乡村的看法完全得到了王室的支持。
我最后得到了王室的印章。
你已经得到王室的印章。

bilingual.source: Cheerleaders for the Royal family were outraged.
bilingual.target: 英国王室的粉丝被信中的言论惹恼了。

bilingual.source: Few of the Western democracies still have a royal family.
bilingual.target: 西方民主制国家中很少还有王室的.

bilingual.source: Purple is the special color to the royal family of ancient Rome.
bilingual.target: 紫色是古罗马王室的特殊颜色。

bilingual.source: Little do we know that we actually are members of the Royal family.
bilingual.target: 我们不知道，事实上我们乃是王室的成员之一呢。

list.abstract: Royal，英语单词，是王室的，王族成员的意思，可作形容词或名词使用。

yingyinNormal.en: Oh. I'm most terribly sorry, your royal highness.
yingyinNormal.zh: 噢，我感到非常的抱歉，皇后陛下。

yingyinNormal.en: Oh, there's my prize. The royal blue tang fish. $500.
yingyinNormal.zh: 那是我的珍宝，我的品蓝色拟刺尾鲷，花了五百块呢。

yingyinNormal.en: Not easy to picture you making a deal with a royal.
yingyinNormal.zh: 真想不到你居然会跟皇族合作。

yingyinNormal.en: There are eight Royal Parks, and many of them are in central London, and close to royal palaces and other historic monuments.
yingyinNormal.zh: 伦敦有八座皇家公园﹐当中大部份都是位于伦敦中部，并且邻近皇宫及其他历史遗迹。

yingyinNormal.en: So you just meant like the royal "we"? Yep. That's right.
yingyinNormal.zh: 那你这是广义的"我们"?是的，对。

yingyinNormal.en: The royal baby smiled at the queen. I meant at the diner.
yingyinNormal.zh: 英国皇室宝宝会对着女王笑了。我指的是这家餐厅。

yingyinNormal.en: Another legacy of England's monarchy are the Royal Parks of London.
yingyinNormal.zh: 而伦敦皇家公园则是另一个英格兰皇室遗留下来的景点。

yingyinNormal.en: I was invited to the royal wedding. I thought we were speaking truth.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我受邀参加王室婚礼。我们不是要说亮话吗？

yingyinNormal.en: I was once your age. I know the dreams that cloud a royal virgin's head. I may have wondered.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我也曾像你这么大，我知道年轻的皇家女子会做些什么美梦。我也想过。

yingyinNormal.en: No, it's even funnier. Uh, so you know how hard I've been working on the Grand Royal Hotel account?
yingyinNormal.zh: 不，其实更有意思。你知道我一直在努力争取皇家大饭店这个客户吧？

yingyinNormal.en: Not in the face, though, please. I promised my brain to the Royal Society. Where would you suggest?
yingyinNormal.zh: 但请你别打脸。我承诺把脑子给皇家学会了。那你觉得应该打哪？

yingyinNormal.en: I am no royal. When the Khan's men attacked the Bayaut, I was a peasant girl, serving in the palace.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我不是什么公主，大汗的军队袭击巴牙兀惕部落时，我只是个普通女子，在宫殿里做侍女。

yingyinNormal.en: Hear ye! Hear ye! Quiet! Know, on this day, two weeks hence, there shall be held, at the palace, a Royal Ball.
yingyinNormal.zh: 大家听着，都听着！安静！敬请周知，两周后的今天，在王宫将会举行一场皇家舞会。

yingyinNormal.en: Just behind the Opera House, on the site of Sydney's first farm are the Royal Botanic Gardens and the Sydney Domain.
yingyinNormal.zh: 歌剧院的后面有悉尼第一个农场，而这里则是悉尼皇家植物园和领地公园的所在地。

yingyinNormal.en: He's got a burn-mark on his right hand. You fought in the army. Iraq. Royal Irish Regiment. Two tours, Special Forces.
yingyinNormal.zh: 他的右手上有一处烧伤疤痕。你参过军。在伊拉克执勤过。隶属于皇家爱尔兰军团。参加过两次战斗，是特种部队的。

yingyinNormal.en: They were once reserved as private hunting grounds for the royal family, but nowadays they're open for everyone to enjoy.
yingyinNormal.zh: 曾经这座公园只是给皇室成员打猎之用，到了今天则已开放给公众游览。

yingyinNormal.en: It is the king I am thinking of. It would be an insult to the royal personage to take you to the palace dressed in these old rags.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这正是我所担心的，如果你穿着这一身旧破布去宫里见皇室要员，那可是极大的不尊重。

yingyinNormal.en: What does that matter? The fact is that the Royal Yorkshire County Hospital wants to take over our little hospital, which is outrageous.
yingyinNormal.zh: 这有什么关系？重点是约克郡皇家医院想接管我们的小医院，这也太过分了。

yingyinNormal.en: Our royal family will attend the private services in St. James's palace the morning of with 28 other heads of state from all over the globe.
yingyinNormal.zh: 皇室成员当天早晨会在圣詹姆斯宫参加一个私人拜会，其余28位各国首脑届时也会一同出席。

yingyinNormal.en: Commander Denniston, Royal Navy. All right, Mr. Turing, I'll bite. Why do you wish to work for His Majesty's government? Oh, I don't, really.
yingyinNormal.zh: 丹尼斯顿指挥官，皇家海军。好吧，图灵先生，我服了你了。你为什么想为政府工作？哦，其实，我真的不想。

<highlight> 考纲释义</highlight>
精选全国考研考纲词汇、单词义项，由搜狗大数据与考纲、历年真题进行匹配。

<highlight>真题例句</highlight>

examination_example.sentence: A recent paper, titled "The Natural Selection of Bad Science", published on the <highlight>Royal</highlight> Society's open science website, attempts to answer this intriguing and important question.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 最近发表在皇家学会开放科学网站上的一篇题为《不良科学的自然选择》的论文，试图回答这个有趣而重要的问题。

examination_example.sentence: Most <highlight>royal</highlight> families have survived because they allow voters to avoid the difficult search for a non-controversial but respected public figure.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 大多数王室得以幸存，是因为他们让选民不必费力地寻找一个没有争议而受人尊敬的公众人物。

examination_example.sentence: Does that mean the writing is on the wall for all European <highlight>royals</highlight>, with their magnificent uniforms and majestic lifestyles?
examination_example.sentence_trans: 这是否意味着，对所有身着华丽服饰、过着高贵生活的欧洲皇室而言，都将大难临头呢?

word_usage.usage: royal作形容词，表示“国王的；皇家的；王室的”时，只能用于名词之前，修饰该名词，如：the royal family 皇室。
royal作名词，其复数形式royals，表示“王室成员”。

examination_example.sentence: In his short lifetime, which ended exactly 184 years ago today, he would forever revolutionize French gourmet food (美食) , write best-selling cook books and think up magical dishes for <highlight>royals</highlight> and other important people.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 在他短暂的一生中(距今184年前才结束)，他将永远改变法国的美食，写最畅销的烹饪书，并为皇室成员和其他重要人物制作神奇的菜肴。

examination_example.sentence: It was purchased by the <highlight>Royal</highlight> family.
Soon, members of the <highlight>royal</highlight> family and other wealthy people took up motoring as a sport.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 很快，皇室成员和其他富人开始把开车作为一项运动。

examination_example.sentence: The <highlight>Royal</highlight> Society of Public Health discovered that music and art, when used in hospitals, help to improve the conditions of patients.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 皇家公共卫生协会发现，音乐和艺术在医院使用时，有助于改善病人的状况。

examination_example.sentence: Visit the city with over 2, 000 years of history and Bath Abbey, the <highlight>Royal</highlight> Crescent and the Costume Museum.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 参观这座拥有2000多年历史的城市，还有巴斯修道院、皇家新月会和服装博物馆。

examination_example.sentence: Now this former <highlight>royal</highlight> palace is open to the public as a major tourist attraction.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 现在这座前皇家宫殿作为一个主要的旅游景点向公众开放。
